						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall, <hi rend="italic">ardhamaṇḍapa</hi> Saundarēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 8: 979 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records a gift of a perpetual lamp by <hi rend="italic">Ayyapoḻil-aiññūṟṟuvar</hi> of Kāmaravallichchaturvēdimaṅgalam in honour of their servant Kuṟumbaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Maṇamēṟkuḍichchiṅgamvaḷañjiyar of Viḍēlviḍugu-[chaturvēdimaṅgalam] in Takkaḷūr-nāḍu, who seems to have been killed in a fight.</p>						

						</summary>
